# Journey planning link

LinkShelf **implementation** lives in this repo (`fj-linkshelf`). The sibling **Journey** repo (`fullstack-journey`) holds high-level phase plans — not application code.

## Planning docs

| What | Path (from repo root) |
|------|------------------------|
| Project overview | `../fullstack-journey/projects/linkshelf/README.md` |
| High-level phase plans (Journey) | `../fullstack-journey/projects/linkshelf/phase-*.md` |
| Detailed execution plans (this repo) | `.cursor/plans/phase-*.md` — phase-0 bootstrap, phase-1 study build |

## Workflow

End-to-end flow for a phase:

1. **Journey — high-level plan:** Create or maintain `projects/linkshelf/phase-<N>.md` (outcomes, scope, checklist).
2. **Journey — detailed plan:** Invoke `@fj-plan-on-project` with the phase file attached → writes `.cursor/plans/phase-<N>.md` here with defined steps and step completion tracking.
3. **Project — execute:** Invoke `@fj-ls-execute-next-step` once. It reads the detailed plan, picks the next step, and implements a **commit-sized** chunk. Refine the output if needed, **commit** the result, then invoke again for the next step. Repeat until all steps are `done`.
4. **Project — review:** Invoke `@fj-ls-review` for a PR-level review against the detailed plan, Journey phase file, and project rules. Call it as many times as needed (back-and-forth fixes, missing items, etc.).
5. **Project — wrap up:** Invoke `@fj-ls-wrap-up` to run quality checks (tests if applicable, lint, typecheck, formatting), ask permission to push, and draft or update the PR description.

**Journey shipping** (checklist ticks, Journey-only changes): `@fj-wrap-up` in the Journey repo — separate from `@fj-ls-wrap-up`.

## Skills (this repo)

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `@fj-ls-execute-next-step` | Implement the next plan step (one invocation = one step) |
| `@fj-ls-review` | PR-level review; read-only unless user asks to fix gaps |
| `@fj-ls-wrap-up` | Quality gates, push (with permission), PR description |

## Stack (interview study)

Single Next.js App Router app, PostgreSQL (Docker + Drizzle), plain REST Route Handlers, Tailwind CSS. **Dry setup** — no monorepo, no real auth (user switcher only). See Journey overview for interview topic map.

## Rules

- All application code, configs, and tests belong in **`fj-linkshelf` only**.
- Do **not** add implementation files under `fullstack-journey/projects/linkshelf/`.
- Each execute step should produce work sized for a single commit before the next `@fj-ls-execute-next-step`.
- When Journey checklist items are complete, tick them in `phase-*.md` in the Journey repo; commit each repo separately.

## Workspace

Develop with both repos open: `../fullstack-journey/fullstack-journey.code-workspace`.
